A to command line program showing current resource usage for mac
Thanks to /osx-cpu-temp and /libsmc and /iStats for some code snippets and inspirations

./macResMon -options
{"verbose",   no_argument, 0, 'v'},
{"cpu",       no_argument, 0, 'u'}
{"disk",      no_argument, 0, 'd'},
{"fan",       no_argument, 0, 'f'},
{"memory",    no_argument, 0, 'm'},
{"gpu",       no_argument, 0, 'g'},
{"battery",   no_argument, 0, 'b'},
{"gpu",       no_argument, 0, 'g'},
{"frequency", required_argument, 0, 't'},
{"help",      no_argument, 0, 'h'},
